After what felt like hours of falling through the void, you finally wake up to a blurry first sight of your new surroundings. The expansive colums of shelves, where no end can be seen beyond the horizon, is nearly enough for someone to shiver. Except when you have been a traveler of the Backrooms for nearly 2 years, where a distorted layout like this one is seen nearly every day. Managing to stand up, you cough dust particles away, and give out a long sight.

The only thing you can do, and your first instinct upon landing, is to keep moving. If the Backrooms has taught you something, it is that you shouldn´t stay on the same spot for too long. That, with the hope of finding people, makes you want to go on a full-on sprint in search for the outposts located somewhere throughout. The distant, distorted music rings in your ears, repeating on itself every once in a while. You don´t mind much, though.

Trudging onwards, whilst blinded by the white lights on the ceiling, the idea of other people in this level starts to fade away. Your fingers hold tightly to the Major Navigation System, which beyond its dim light, it reads:

<div style="background:rgba(0,0,0,0.5); margin:auto; border:2px solid #fff; color:white; padding:1rem;width:80%">
[[File:MEGNOTICES.png|250px|center|link=]]
<div style="font-size:20px"><center>You are currently on:</center></div>
<div style="font-size:28px"><center>'''Level 114: The Infamart'''</center></div>
<div style="font-size:23px"><center>Destination: The M.E.G Infamart Haven in 40km</center></div>
<div style="font-size:20px"><center>Safety is near.</center></div>
</div><br><br>


There is hope...

</div></div>

<div style="background-color: #000000; color: #ffffff; border: 2px solid #fff; position: relative; overflow: hidden; padding: 30px 20px; margin: 5px 10px; margin-bottom: 20px;">
<div style="position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; opacity: {{{opacity|0.50}}}">[[File:Black-Screen.png|2000px|link=]]</div><div style="position: relative; margin: 4px;">
{{Blurimage|file=Screenshot 20240610-124404~2.png|caption=|width=600px|align=center}}


Level 114, colloquially known as "The Infamart" by most wanderers, takes the shape of a singular biome: an expansive supermarket similar to those found in Baseline Reality. The floors are made of white tiles, while the walls, although rare to encounter, are usually a light shade of beige or tan. The ceilings are mostly adorned with industrial ceiling lights that illuminate the level, although certain sections of the level are known to lack these lights, remaining dark instead.

Shelves and freezers can be found in almost every area of the level, whether it be on rows or simply scattered throughout individually in a disorganized maner. All of these shelves and freezers are known to be mostly empty, although certain rows have been documented to hold certain items common to the Backrooms, such as [[Object 1|Almond Water]] and canned goods.

Speakers within some walls are known to play music. These kinds of music always fit within the subgenre of mallsoft (mall music), although in rare occasions the music has shifted genre for small amounts of time. There have been instances of the music stopping abruptly, only to be replaced with a series of random musical notes. Other anomalies have been documented throughout the speakers of Level 114. These include sounds from other levels, such as the buzzing from [[level 0]] or wood creaking presumably from [[Level 27]].

Ever since the events of [[Phenomenon 12|The Flicker]], small Blackout events have ocurred every few months within the level. These blackouts shut down all the power of the level, leaving it dark unless lit by an external source. Although not entirely dangerous, as there have not been any reported entities, the temperatures have been documented to decrease significantly, usually reaching freezing point. Additionally, the shopping carts within the expanse have been heard moving, although any actual documentation of these moving is yet to be taken.

There have been rumors of a checkout area within the deep sections of Level 114, spanning for a large distance. In contrast with the rest of the level, it is said that this section is filled with exclusive items such as snack bags. These lanes show small quantities of items throughout the floors or within them, suggesting that at one point in time the Infamart may have been filled with foodstuffs and other items.

Said rumors also talk about exit doors that can be found in these indefinite checkout lane, leading into some sort of exterior area. Based on the reports given to the M.E.G, this "outside" resembles some sort of foggy rooftop parking lot, lined with streetlamps that emmit diferent colored lights. As there has only been one report of this area, all claims of any checkout space, as well as an outside, remain entirely uncomfirmed.

Employee-only rooms can be rarely found throughout the level, accessed through a wide variety of doors. These rooms, unlike the rest of the level, are usually filled with items, which are stored in drawers or vending machines. Apart from their large quantities of items, these rooms also hold heaters, making them points of interest to be on the lookout for during a Blackout.

Level 114 has been, over the past years, a hot spot for small colonies and outposts from various groups, including the [[M.E.G.|M.E.G]] and the [[Republic of Aurielle]]. This has led to small firefights between the two groups, although there have not been any casualties yet. Nonetheless, even if these fights happen from time to time, most groups don´t interact with each other. Even if these bases do exist, finding them is nearly impossible due to the indefinite size of the level.

The most prevalent outpost within the level is the '''M.E.G Infamart Haven'''. This outpost is known to hold a large array of items, which have been imported from other outposts, as well as certain types of weaponry. The base is mostly centered around trading and bringing wanderers into other safe levels, although as mentioned earlier, the base tries to remove enemy bases from the level as well.

==Entrances==
* Entering a store with the 7-Eleven logo sends one here from [[Level 624]].
* Certain areas within [[Level 296]] bring one here.
* Numerous elevators scattered through [[Level 810]] have been documented to lead here.
* Finding a retail store in [[Level 33]] labeled "Freshly Frozen Foods" and entering it will bring wanderers here.
* Elevators in [[Level 113]] may lead here.
==Exits==
* Some employee-only rooms can shift randomly into either [[Level 526]] or [[Level 156]].

