==Description==

{{Blurimage|file=Crashing bar.png|caption=<center>A Crashbar with its wrapping</center>|hovertext=One of the best foodstuffs in the entirety of the Backrooms!}} 

"Jelly Rations" are an anomalous object that can be found in Level 114, usually in small quantities. Their appearance is that of an opaque ingot similar to a crash bar of some sort. These objects all hold a somewhat jellatenous form, slightly wobbling upon moderate force being applied to them. As of current times, all of these items have been found covered up in blue wrapping, being labeled as "Crash Bars" solely in the paper. Further inspections have been taken, especially on the Ingredients list. The wrapping displays the bar as being made of Almond water, Mixologist´s Delight, and certain other anomalous compounds, all thickened into its plasma-like substance. Manufactering details are non-existent as of current times.

Upon consumed, Anomalous Crash Bars can give many benefits to one´s body. These include a boost of energy for nearly 2 hours, making them useful while having to traverse large distances. Additionally, these bars also can act as a replacement of a short meal, holding nearly 600 calories per unit. Anomalous properties can be also seen after eating, such as the relieve of minor headaches, therefore functioning similarly to  acetaminophen.

Based on tests, all bars lack a strong taste, holding a neutral flavor, similarly to water. Nevertheless, certain ones have been documented to hold a small hint of either lemon or vanilla, presumably from the compounds of the bar. As of texture, the crash bars seems durable at first, with only its slight, aforementiomed wobbling. Nevertheless, if contact with water or any sort of liquid is made, the bars becomes much more gelatenous than before.

Due to the benefits of Jelly Rations, the [[M.E.G.|M.E.G]] has set out a plan to use these objects to their advantage, using them as basic food supply for exploring divisions such as Voyager and Volunteer Squad. In fact, the large quantity of these items, as well as its nutritional benefits, leaves expectations for it to become nearly as popular as basic items such as [[Object 1|Almond Water.]]

Ever since its discovery, many groups have created more settlements on the Infamart, although they are still very hard to encounter. While this has built up more tension between the M.E.G and The Republic of Aurielle, no armed conflict has been taken.
